gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 147, Wizards 106
gameRecap.excerpt: The Thunder win their fourth game in a row as they defeat the Wizards, 147-106, and move to 39-17 on the year. 147 points marks a new season high as the Thunder were led by Shai Gilgeous-Alexander (30 points, nine assists, seven rebounds) and Chet Holmgren (25 points on 11-14 FG, 10 rebounds, two blocks) as the team went 55-92 overall (59.7%). Jordan Poole (21 points) and Corey Kispert (20 points) led the Wizards in the loss. Washington moves to 9-47 on the year.
